There are a number of important implications of using the dipole groups: (i) the hydrogen bonds via the COOH groups within the planes restrict the electronic transport and dissipation of energy in the directions perpendicular to the photovoltaic path, (ii) the polarization generated across the solar device orders the energy levels in a cascade [6], (iii) the electronic transport along the π\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
