				\begin{document}$$\pi $$\end{document}-conjugated rings for the electrons, and holes move between the dipole groups [7], (iv) an adsorption of the optically active molecules at the surfaces of the transparent conductive oxides, used as the electrodes, leads to the high power conversion when it is realized with the COOH group [28]. Therefore, it is useful to examine various dipole groups for their impact on the energy gaps. In Table 1, the dipole moments in the direction parallel to the photovoltaic transport for all studied groups attached to one aromatic ring are collected.Table 1
