A collection of molecules with various lengths of the aromatic chains is gathered in Fig. 2. The energy gaps are presented on a scale of the Sun radiation activity from the soft ultraviolet (350 nm) to the far infrared of a cloudy sky (1400 nm). The impact of various dipole groups on the LUMO–HOMO energy difference does not change with the group types, when they are attached to the long chains (above five benzene rings). Moreover, increasing a number of the dipole groups does not change the energy gap for the longer molecules. Due to the lack of this effect, we can focus on the transport properties when a design of the dipole groups is considered.Figure 2
